         </tbody>
      </table>

       <h5>How to Use</h5>
<p><b>What is Warning Message?</b><br>A warning message is to alert users of a condition that might cause a problem in the future.</p>

	<p><b>Characteristic of a good warning message</b></p>
	<p></p>Involve risk. Good warnings alert users of something significant.<br>E.g:Are you sure to want to delete the driver and all its data?</p>
	<p>Have immediate relevance<br>E.g:The account will be blocked with 5 times incorrect password input to prevent hackers!</p>
	<p>Lead to action. There is something users must do or be aware of as the result of the warning. Warnings without actions just make users feel paranoid.<br>E.g: Your account will be blocked! The message will make users confused and don't understand why?</p>
	<p>Be clear and specific. Read the warning message, users can know:</p>
	<li>The source of the warning. E.g Use the title to know where the warning came from</li>
	<li>The specific condition and potential problem.</li>
	<li>What the user should do about it.</li>
	<li>What happens if the user doesn't do anything.</li>
	<br>
	<p><b>What should be avoided in a warning message?</b></p>
	<p>Redundant message<br>Overwarning that makes your program feel hazardous and look lije it was designed by lawyers.</p>
	
      <h3><a name="S3"></a><span>Information Message</span></h3>
          <h5>Template</h5>
<div class="modal" style="position: relative; top: auto; left: auto; margin: 0 auto 20px; z-index: 1; max-width: 100%;">
<div class="modal-header">
<button class="close" aria-hidden="true" data-dismiss="modal" type="button">×</button>
<h3>Information</h3>
</div>
<div class="modal-body">
<p><span class="label label-info">Info</span>
<p>Your resgistration is completed. Please check your email inbox to activate your account!</p>
</div>
<div class="modal-footer">
<a class="btn btn-info" href="#">OK</a>
</div>
</div>

<div id="myModal2" class="modal hide fade" aria-hidden="true" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel" role="dialog" tabindex="-1" style="display: block;">
