       <h5>How to Use</h5>
<p><b>What is Confirmation Message?</b></p>
	<p>A confirmation message is to ask if the user wants to proceed with an action.<br>The display of a confirmation can be in a default browser pop-up or in a customized pop up window like the same template above.<br>With the deletion confirmation that may damage to huge data such as delete a forum, all its topics/post will be lost. The confirmation should be a warning that display in a pop up (like the template above) rather than using browser pop-up to warn the importance of the current action.
       </p>
	<p><b>Characteristic of a good confirmation message</b></p>
	<li>Obvious result display of an action initiated by the user.</li>
	<li>Relevant verification if the user wants to proceed with the action.</li>
	<li>Simple question and two or more responses.</li>
	<p>If a confirmation involves risk, it can be considered a warning as well. It is great to use a customized pop-up window rather than a default browser pop-up.</p>

	<p><b>What should be avoided in a confirmation message?</b></p>
	<li>Unnecessary confirmation.<br>E.g: Are you sure to rename the file?</li>
	<li>Annoying confirmation.<br>E.g: There is no change on the form. However, when clicking on close form. there is confirmation "Are you sure to close the form? "</li>
	<li>Redundant confirmation<br>E.g: Some actions we can redo, recover the old content by revision or from the trash, it is no need to have deletion confirmation </li>
	<br>
     <h3><a name="WUTP"></a><span>Why to Use This Pattern?</span></h3>
     <p>Messages is a way an application talk to end users. So, messages play an important role to make the success of an application.<br>
	Currently, the way to display messages in eXo is inconsistent and incorrect. This pattern is a useful reference to differentiate message types.<br>
	We need to use this pattern to improve message system in eXo. The consistency of message content, style sheet and design will make eXo products look more professional.</p>

